cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CL

The paper proposes a novel generative model for mining human mobility patterns from traffic trajectories. This involves latent factor modeling, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of this model in applications such as latent factor analysis and next location prediction, which are relevant to "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) and "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) respectively. The paper also deals with data management and analysis, which falls under "cs.DB" (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses natural language processing techniques for text data, which is relevant to "cs.CL" (Computation and Language).
